15 Sec. Y-1. 22 MRSA §3197 is enacted to read:
16 §3197. Able-bodied, childless adults; temporary enrollment freeze; permanent
17 enrollment cap
18 Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, the following provisions apply
19 to Medicaid enrollment levels for enrollees who are classified as able-bodied, childless
20 adults.
21 1. Temporary enrollment freeze. Contingent on approval of a Section 1115
22 demonstration waiver under the United States Social Security Act from the United States
23 Department of Health and Human Services, Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services,
24 within 30 days of the effective date of this section, the total number of MaineCare enrollees
25 classified as able-bodied, childless adults that may be enrolled in the MaineCare program
26 must be frozen and the enrollment level may not be increased. New enrollments of able-
27 bodied, childless adults may not be made until the department has certified that the total
28 enrollment in this category has been reduced by 10% from the level of enrollment at the
29 date enrollment is frozen under this subsection.
30 2. Enrollment reduction. When an enrollee becomes ineligible for MaineCare
31 coverage, that enrollee may not be automatically reenrolled. When an enrollee's eligibility
32 lapses due to income increase, employment or failure to renew enrollment, that enrollee's
33 spot in the program may not be filled by a new enrollee. The department shall prioritize
34 program integrity measures to remove ineligible enrollees.
35 3. Lifting enrollment freeze; permanent enrollment cap. When the total enrollment
36 of able-bodied, childless adults has declined by 10% from the number of enrollments at the
37 time of the enrollment freeze pursuant to subsection 1, the reduced level of enrollment is
